University Press, pp. 392&ndash;417.</li>

<li>Runzo, Joseph, 1988, &ldquo;God, Commitment, and Other Faiths:
Pluralism vs. Relativism&rdquo;, <em>Faith and Philosophy</em>, 5:
343&ndash;364.</li>

<li>Schoenfield, Miriam, 2019, &ldquo;Permissivism and the Value of
Rationality: A Challenge to the Uniqueness Thesis&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophy and Phenomenological Research</em>, 99:
286&ndash;297.</li>

<li>Sharma, Arvind, 2011, &ldquo;A Hindu Perspective&rdquo;, in
<em>The Oxford Handbook of Religious Diversity</em>, Chad Meister
(ed.), Oxford: Oxford University Press, pp. 309&ndash;320.</li>

<li>Tracy, David, 1995, <em>Blessed Rage of Order</em>: <em>The New
Pluralism in Theology</em>, Chicago: University of Chicago Press.</li>

<li>van Inwagen, Peter, 1996, &ldquo;It is Wrong, Everywhere, Always,
and for Anyone, to Believe Anything Upon Insufficient Evidence&rdquo;,
